wfAppleBaseDebugLevel.description: Appletalk has control of what debug and info messages are printed.

wfAppleBaseEstimatedHosts.name: wfAppleBaseEstimatedHosts
wfAppleBaseEstimatedHosts.description: This parameter indicates the estimated number of end stations that the router will need to keep in its AARP table. This should not include end stations that are reached through another router.

wfAppleMacIPServerResponces.name: wfAppleMacIPServerResponces
wfAppleMacIPServerResponces.description: The Number of times this router has responded to server requests.

wfAppleRtmpTable.name: wfAppleRtmpTable
wfAppleRtmpTable.description: The table of elements of AppleTalk's routing RTMP table

wfAppleRtmpEntry.name: wfAppleRtmpEntry
wfAppleRtmpEntry.description: An entry in the Routing table

wfAppleRtmpNetStart.name: wfAppleRtmpNetStart
wfAppleRtmpNetStart.description: The destinatination network range of this route to which this entry pertains. The route is considered the best route to that network. There wil only be one route to a single destination. The address will be in the form of [network min - network max].

wfAppleRtmpNetEnd.name: wfAppleRtmpNetEnd
wfAppleRtmpNetEnd.description: The network max in the destination network range to which the routing entry pertains.

wfAppleRtmpPort.name: wfAppleRtmpPort
wfAppleRtmpPort.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfAppleRtmpHops.name: wfAppleRtmpHops
wfAppleRtmpHops.description: The routing metric to get to this destination network. The measurement is in terms of hops.

wfAppleRtmpNextHopNet.name: wfAppleRtmpNextHopNet
wfAppleRtmpNextHopNet.description: The AppleTalk net of the next hop router for this route.

wfAppleRtmpNextHopNode.name: wfAppleRtmpNextHopNode
wfAppleRtmpNextHopNode.description: The AppleTalk node of the next hop router for this route.

wfAppleRtmpState.name: wfAppleRtmpState
wfAppleRtmpState.description: The state of this routing entry: 1 = Good, 2 = Suspect, 3 = GoingBad, or 4 = Bad.

wfAppleRtmpProto.name: wfAppleRtmpProto
wfAppleRtmpProto.description: The protocol this routing entry was learned through: 1 = RTMP, 2 = AURP, 3 = Static Route.

wfAppleRtmpAurpNextHopIpAddress.name: wfAppleRtmpAurpNextHopIpAddress
wfAppleRtmpAurpNextHopIpAddress.description: The next hop address if this route was learned through AURP.

wfApplePortTable.name: wfApplePortTable
wfApplePortTable.description: The port descriptor table that describes the configuration parameters for this port of the AppleTalk Router.

wfApplePortEntry.name: wfApplePortEntry
wfApplePortEntry.description: An entry in the Port Descriptor table

wfApplePortDelete.name: wfApplePortDelete
wfApplePortDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object to create/delete an AppleTalk interface. The default is create.

wfApplePortDisable.name: wfApplePortDisable
wfApplePortDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Users perforn an SNMP SET operation on this object to enable/disable an AppleTalk interface. Default is enabled.

wfApplePortCircuit.name: wfApplePortCircuit
wfApplePortCircuit.description: The circuit number for this interface

wfApplePortState.name: wfApplePortState
wfApplePortState.description: The current state of the AppleTalk port.

wfApplePortType.name: wfApplePortType
wfApplePortType.description: wfApplePortType is reserved for future use

wfApplePortCksumDisable.name: wfApplePortCksumDisable
wfApplePortCksumDisable.description: Flag to enable/disable the calculation of the DDP checksum for packets sourced by the router over this interface. This value has no effect on incoming packets.

wfApplePortTrEndStation.name: wfApplePortTrEndStation
wfApplePortTrEndStation.description: When an interface is running token ring this attribute allows for end station source routing. If the interface is not running token ring the attribute has no meaning.

wfApplePortGniForever.name: wfApplePortGniForever
wfApplePortGniForever.description: wfApplePortGniForever is ignored. A non-seed interface will send GetNetInfos every 10 seconds until it gets a response.

wfApplePortAarpFlush.name: wfApplePortAarpFlush
wfApplePortAarpFlush.description: The maximum age (in minutes) of an aarp entry before it is deleted. Defaults to 12 hours. Minimum values is five minutes.

wfApplePortNodeId.name: wfApplePortNodeId
wfApplePortNodeId.description: The AppleTalk node id configured for this port/interface. If PortNodeId or PortNetwork is zero the interface will try to acquire an address dynamically.

wfApplePortNetwork.name: wfApplePortNetwork
wfApplePortNetwork.description: The AppleTalk network number configured for this port/interface. If PortNodeId or PortNetwork is zero the interface will try to acquire an address dynamically.

wfApplePortNetStart.name: wfApplePortNetStart
wfApplePortNetStart.description: The Network start value in the network range for this interface/port. If this is zero, the port is considered non-seed.

wfApplePortNetEnd.name: wfApplePortNetEnd
wfApplePortNetEnd.description: The Network end value in the network range for this interface/port.

wfApplePortDfltZone.name: wfApplePortDfltZone
wfApplePortDfltZone.description: The default zone name for this network range/ interface.

wfApplePortCurNodeId.name: wfApplePortCurNodeId
wfApplePortCurNodeId.description: The AppleTalk node id of this port

wfApplePortCurNetwork.name: wfApplePortCurNetwork
wfApplePortCurNetwork.description: The network number for this port.

wfApplePortCurNetStart.name: wfApplePortCurNetStart
wfApplePortCurNetStart.description: The Network start value in the network range for this port.

wfApplePortCurNetEnd.name: wfApplePortCurNetEnd
wfApplePortCurNetEnd.description: The Network end value in the network range for this port.

wfApplePortCurDfltZone.name: wfApplePortCurDfltZone
wfApplePortCurDfltZone.description: The default zone name for this port

wfApplePortAarpProbeRxs.name: wfApplePortAarpProbeRxs
wfApplePortAarpProbeRxs.description: The number of AARP Probe packets received on this interface.

wfApplePortAarpProbeTxs.name: wfApplePortAarpProbeTxs
wfApplePortAarpProbeTxs.description: The number of AARP Probe packets transmitted on this interface.

wfApplePortAarpReqRxs.name: wfApplePortAarpReqRxs
wfApplePortAarpReqRxs.description: The number of AARP Request packets received on this interface.

wfApplePortAarpReqTxs.name: wfApplePortAarpReqTxs
wfApplePortAarpReqTxs.description: The number of AARP Request packets transmitted on this interface.

wfApplePortAarpRspRxs.name: wfApplePortAarpRspRxs
wfApplePortAarpRspRxs.description: The number of AARP Response packets received on this interface.

wfApplePortAarpRspTxs.name: wfApplePortAarpRspTxs
wfApplePortAarpRspTxs.description: The number of AARP Response packets transmitted on this interface.

wfApplePortDdpOutRequests.name: wfApplePortDdpOutRequests
wfApplePortDdpOutRequests.description: The total number of DDP datagrams which were supplied to DDP by local DDP clients in requests for transmission. Note that this counter does not include any datagrams counted in ddpForwRequests.

wfApplePortDdpInReceives.name: wfApplePortDdpInReceives
wfApplePortDdpInReceives.description: The total number of input datagrams received by DDP, including those received in error.

wfApplePortDdpInLocalDatagrams.name: wfApplePortDdpInLocalDatagrams
wfApplePortDdpInLocalDatagrams.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams for which this entity was their final DDP destination.

wfApplePortDdpNoProtocolHandlers.name: wfApplePortDdpNoProtocolHandlers
wfApplePortDdpNoProtocolHandlers.description: The total number of DDP datagrams addressed to this entity that were addressed to an upper layer protocol for which no protocol handler existed.

wfApplePortDdpTooShortErrors.name: wfApplePortDdpTooShortErrors
wfApplePortDdpTooShortErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams dropped because the received data length was less than the data length specified in the DDP header or the received data length was less than the length of the expected DDP header.

wfApplePortDdpTooLongErrors.name: wfApplePortDdpTooLongErrors
wfApplePortDdpTooLongErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams dropped because the received data length was greater than the data length specified in the DDP header or because they exceeded the maximum DDP datagram size.

wfApplePortDdpChecksumErrors.name: wfApplePortDdpChecksumErrors
wfApplePortDdpChecksumErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams for which this DDP entity was their final destination, and which were dropped because of a checksum error.

wfApplePortDdpForwRequests.name: wfApplePortDdpForwRequests
wfApplePortDdpForwRequests.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final DDP destination, as a result of which an attempt was made to find a route to forward them to that final destination.

wfApplePortDdpOutNoRoutes.name: wfApplePortDdpOutNoRoutes
wfApplePortDdpOutNoRoutes.description: The total number of DDP datagrams dropped because a route could not be found to their final destination.

wfApplePortDdpBroadcastErrors.name: wfApplePortDdpBroadcastErrors
wfApplePortDdpBroadcastErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams dropped because this entity was not their final destination and they were addressed to the link level broadcast.

wfApplePortDdpHopCountErrors.name: wfApplePortDdpHopCountErrors
wfApplePortDdpHopCountErrors.description: The total number of input DDP datagrams dropped because this entity was not their final destination and their hop count would exceed 15.

wfApplePortRtmpInDataPkts.name: wfApplePortRtmpInDataPkts
wfApplePortRtmpInDataPkts.description: A count of the number of good RTMP data packets received by this entity.

wfApplePortRtmpOutDataPkts.name: wfApplePortRtmpOutDataPkts
wfApplePortRtmpOutDataPkts.description: A count of the number of RTMP packets sent by this entity.

wfApplePortRtmpInRequestPkts.name: wfApplePortRtmpInRequestPkts
wfApplePortRtmpInRequestPkts.description: A count of the number of good RTMP Request packets received by this entity.

wfApplePortRtmpNextIREqualChanges.name: wfApplePortRtmpNextIREqualChanges
wfApplePortRtmpNextIREqualChanges.description: A count of the number of times RTMP changes the Next Internet Router in a routing entry because the hop count advertised in a routing tuple was equal to the current hop count for a particular network.

wfApplePortRtmpNextIRLessChanges.name: wfApplePortRtmpNextIRLessChanges
wfApplePortRtmpNextIRLessChanges.description: A count of the number of times RTMP changes the Next Internet Router in a routing entry because the hop count advertised in a routing tuple was less than the current hop count for a particular network.

wfApplePortRtmpRouteDeletes.name: wfApplePortRtmpRouteDeletes
wfApplePortRtmpRouteDeletes.description: A count of the number of times RTMP deletes a route because it was aged out of the table. This can help to detect routing problems.

wfApplePortRtmpNetworkMismatchErrors.name: wfApplePortRtmpNetworkMismatchErrors
wfApplePortRtmpNetworkMismatchErrors.description: The number of times RTMP receives a Data packet from a router who claims to be on a different network than that configured for the receiving port. This can help to detect configuration errors.

wfApplePortRtmpRoutingTableOverflows.name: wfApplePortRtmpRoutingTableOverflows
wfApplePortRtmpRoutingTableOverflows.description: The number of times RTMP attempted to add a route to the RTMP table but failed due to overflow.

wfApplePortZipInZipQueries.name: wfApplePortZipInZipQueries
wfApplePortZipInZipQueries.description: The number of ZIP Queries received by this entity.

wfApplePortZipInZipReplies.name: wfApplePortZipInZipReplies
wfApplePortZipInZipReplies.description: The number of ZIP Replies received by this entity.

wfApplePortZipOutZipReplies.name: wfApplePortZipOutZipReplies
wfApplePortZipOutZipReplies.description: The number of ZIP Replies sent by this entity.

wfApplePortZipInZipExtendedReplies.name: wfApplePortZipInZipExtendedReplies
wfApplePortZipInZipExtendedReplies.description: The number of ZIP Extended Replies received by this entity.

wfApplePortZipOutZipExtendedReplies.name: wfApplePortZipOutZipExtendedReplies
wfApplePortZipOutZipExtendedReplies.description: The number of ZIP Extended Replies sent by this entity.

wfApplePortZipInGetZoneLists.name: wfApplePortZipInGetZoneLists
wfApplePortZipInGetZoneLists.description: The number of ZIP GetZoneList transactions received by this entity.

wfApplePortZipOutGetZoneListReplies.name: wfApplePortZipOutGetZoneListReplies
wfApplePortZipOutGetZoneListReplies.description: The number of ZIP GetZoneListReply transactions sent by this entity.

wfApplePortZipInGetLocalZones.name: wfApplePortZipInGetLocalZones
wfApplePortZipInGetLocalZones.description: The number of ZIP GetLocalZone transactions received by this entity.

wfApplePortZipOutGetLocalZoneReplies.name: wfApplePortZipOutGetLocalZoneReplies
wfApplePortZipOutGetLocalZoneReplies.description: The number of ZIP GetLocalZoneReply transactions sent by this entity.

wfApplePortZipInGetMyZones.name: wfApplePortZipInGetMyZones
wfApplePortZipInGetMyZones.description: The number of ZIP GetMyZone transactions received by this entity.

wfApplePortZipOutGetMyZoneReplies.name: wfApplePortZipOutGetMyZoneReplies
wfApplePortZipOutGetMyZoneReplies.description: The number of ZIP GetMyZoneReply transactions sent by this entity.

wfApplePortZipZoneConflictErrors.name: wfApplePortZipZoneConflictErrors
wfApplePortZipZoneConflictErrors.description: The number of times a conflict has been detected between this entity's zone information and another entity's zone information.

wfApplePortZipInGetNetInfos.name: wfApplePortZipInGetNetInfos
wfApplePortZipInGetNetInfos.description: The number of ZIP GetNetInfo packets received on this port by this entity.

wfApplePortZipOutGetNetInfoReplies.name: wfApplePortZipOutGetNetInfoReplies
wfApplePortZipOutGetNetInfoReplies.description: The number of ZIP GetNetInfoReply packets sent out this port by this entity.

wfApplePortZipZoneOutInvalids.name: wfApplePortZipZoneOutInvalids
wfApplePortZipZoneOutInvalids.description: The number of times this entity has sent a ZIP GetNetInfo Reply with the zone invalid bit set in response to a GetNetInfo Request with an invalid zone name.

wfApplePortZipAddressInvalids.name: wfApplePortZipAddressInvalids
wfApplePortZipAddressInvalids.description: The number of times this entity had to broadcast a ZIP GetNetInfo Reply because the GetNetInfo Request had an invalid address.

wfApplePortZipOutGetNetInfos.name: wfApplePortZipOutGetNetInfos
wfApplePortZipOutGetNetInfos.description: The number of ZIP GetNetInfo packets sent out this port by this entity.

wfApplePortZipInGetNetInfoReplies.name: wfApplePortZipInGetNetInfoReplies
wfApplePortZipInGetNetInfoReplies.description: The number of ZIP GetNetInfoReply packets received on this port by this entity.

wfApplePortZipOutZipQueries.name: wfApplePortZipOutZipQueries
wfApplePortZipOutZipQueries.description: The number of ZIP Queries sent by this entity.

wfApplePortZipInErrors.name: wfApplePortZipInErrors
wfApplePortZipInErrors.description: The number of ZIP packets received by this entity that were rejected for any error.

wfApplePortNbpInLookUpRequests.name: wfApplePortNbpInLookUpRequests
wfApplePortNbpInLookUpRequests.description: The number of NBP LookUp Requests received.

wfApplePortNbpInLookUpReplies.name: wfApplePortNbpInLookUpReplies
wfApplePortNbpInLookUpReplies.description: The number of NBP LookUp Replies received.

wfApplePortNbpInBroadcastRequests.name: wfApplePortNbpInBroadcastRequests
wfApplePortNbpInBroadcastRequests.description: The number of NBP Broadcast Requests received.

wfApplePortNbpInForwardRequests.name: wfApplePortNbpInForwardRequests
wfApplePortNbpInForwardRequests.description: The number of NBP Forward Requests received.

wfApplePortNbpOutLookUpRequests.name: wfApplePortNbpOutLookUpRequests
wfApplePortNbpOutLookUpRequests.description: The number of NBP LookUp Requests sent.

wfApplePortNbpOutLookUpReplies.name: wfApplePortNbpOutLookUpReplies
wfApplePortNbpOutLookUpReplies.description: The number of NBP LookUp Replies sent.

wfApplePortNbpOutBroadcastRequests.name: wfApplePortNbpOutBroadcastRequests
wfApplePortNbpOutBroadcastRequests.description: The number of NBP Broadcast Requests sent.

wfApplePortNbpOutForwardRequests.name: wfApplePortNbpOutForwardRequests
wfApplePortNbpOutForwardRequests.description: The number of NBP Forward Requests sent.

wfApplePortNbpRegistrationFailures.name: wfApplePortNbpRegistrationFailures
wfApplePortNbpRegistrationFailures.description: The number of times this node experienced a failure in attempting to register an NBP entity.

wfApplePortNbpInErrors.name: wfApplePortNbpInErrors
wfApplePortNbpInErrors.description: The number of NBP packets received by this entity that were rejected for any error.

wfApplePortEchoRequests.name: wfApplePortEchoRequests
wfApplePortEchoRequests.description: The number of AppleTalk Echo requests received.

wfApplePortEchoReplies.name: wfApplePortEchoReplies
wfApplePortEchoReplies.description: The number of AppleTalk Echo replies sent.

wfApplePortWanBroadcastAddress.name: wfApplePortWanBroadcastAddress
wfApplePortWanBroadcastAddress.description: Frame Relay, SMDS, or ATM broadcast address

wfApplePortWanSplitHorizonDisable.name: wfApplePortWanSplitHorizonDisable
wfApplePortWanSplitHorizonDisable.description: WAN (Frame Relay or ATM) split horizon enabled

wfApplePortZoneFilterType.name: wfApplePortZoneFilterType
wfApplePortZoneFilterType.description: Controls zone filtering on this interface. An allow indicates that any wfAppleZoneFilterEntry is a zone that is allowed on the interface. A deny indicates that any ZoneFilterEntry is a zone that should not be advertised out this interface. No ZoneFilterEntrys indicates that all nets and zones are being advertised.

wfAppleLclZoneTable.name: wfAppleLclZoneTable
wfAppleLclZoneTable.description: The Local Zone table describes a list of zone names s serviced by a particular AppleTalk port/interface. In other words, the list of zone names that are associated with a particular network range.

wfAppleLclZoneEntry.name: wfAppleLclZoneEntry
wfAppleLclZoneEntry.description: An entry in the Local Zone table

wfAppleLclZoneDelete.name: wfAppleLclZoneDelete
wfAppleLclZoneDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter for adding/deleting a zone name to the Local Zone List for a particular AppleTalk network interface.

wfAppleLclZonePortCircuit.name: wfAppleLclZonePortCircuit
wfAppleLclZonePortCircuit.description: The circuit number for the corresponding AppleTalk interface /port for this zone list.

wfAppleLclZoneIndex.name: wfAppleLclZoneIndex
wfAppleLclZoneIndex.description: A unique value for this zone name.

wfAppleLclZoneName.name: wfAppleLclZoneName
wfAppleLclZoneName.description: One of the local zone names defined for this/ interface.

wfAppleAarpTable.name: wfAppleAarpTable
wfAppleAarpTable.description: The AppleTalk Address Translation table contains a mapping of AppleTalk Network addresses to its corresponding physical address.

wfAppleAarpEntry.name: wfAppleAarpEntry
wfAppleAarpEntry.description: An entry in the Address Mapping table

wfAppleAarpIfIndex.name: wfAppleAarpIfIndex
wfAppleAarpIfIndex.description: The unique value for this interface/cct. This value is the same interface as identified by the value of ifIndex.

wfAppleAarpNet.name: wfAppleAarpNet
wfAppleAarpNet.description: The host's AppleTalk address (Net.Nodeid). This address corresponds to the media-dependent 'physical' address for this host.

wfAppleAarpNode.name: wfAppleAarpNode
wfAppleAarpNode.description: The host's AppleTalk address (Net.Nodeid). This address corresponds to the media-dependent 'physical' address for this host.

wfAppleZipTable.name: wfAppleZipTable
wfAppleZipTable.description: The Zone Information table for reachable AppleTalk Networks.

wfAppleZipEntry.name: wfAppleZipEntry
wfAppleZipEntry.description: An entry in the Zone Information table

wfAppleZipZoneNetStart.name: wfAppleZipZoneNetStart
wfAppleZipZoneNetStart.description: The network that starts the range for this entry.

wfAppleZipZoneNetEnd.name: wfAppleZipZoneNetEnd
wfAppleZipZoneNetEnd.description: The network that ends the range for this entry.

wfAppleZipIndex.name: wfAppleZipIndex
wfAppleZipIndex.description: The unique value for this zone name.

wfAppleZipZoneName.name: wfAppleZipZoneName
wfAppleZipZoneName.description: The ASCII xone name of this entry.

wfAppleZipZoneState.name: wfAppleZipZoneState
wfAppleZipZoneState.description: The state of the ZIP entry.

wfAppleZoneFilterTable.name: wfAppleZoneFilterTable
wfAppleZoneFilterTable.description: The zone filter table describes a list of zone names filtered on a given AppleTalk port/interface.

wfAppleZoneFilterEntry.name: wfAppleZoneFilterEntry
wfAppleZoneFilterEntry.description: An entry in the Zone Filter table

wfAppleZoneFilterDelete.name: wfAppleZoneFilterDelete
wfAppleZoneFilterDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter for adding/deleting a zone name to the filter list for a particular AppleTalk network interface.

wfAppleZoneFilterCircuit.name: wfAppleZoneFilterCircuit
wfAppleZoneFilterCircuit.description: The circuit number for the corresponding AppleTalk interface for filtered zone entry. This is only valid if wfAppleZoneFilterCircuitType is RTMP

wfAppleZoneFilterIpAddress.name: wfAppleZoneFilterIpAddress
wfAppleZoneFilterIpAddress.description: The IP address for the corresponding AURP interface for filtered zone entry. This is only valid if wfAppleZoneFilterCircuitType is AURP.

wfAppleZoneFilterCircuitType.name: wfAppleZoneFilterCircuitType
wfAppleZoneFilterCircuitType.description: The type of the circuit the filter is applied on. If RTMP, then wfAppleZoneFilterCircuit is used. If AURP, then wfAppleZoneFilterIpAddress is used.

wfAppleZoneFilterIndex.name: wfAppleZoneFilterIndex
wfAppleZoneFilterIndex.description: A unique value for this filtered zone name.

wfAppleZoneFilterName.name: wfAppleZoneFilterName
wfAppleZoneFilterName.description: One of the zone names filtered on this/ interface.

wfAppleAurpBaseDelete.name: wfAppleAurpBaseDelete
wfAppleAurpBaseDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter for determining whether or not AURP is configured on this box.

wfAppleAurpBaseDisable.name: wfAppleAurpBaseDisable
wfAppleAurpBaseDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter for determining whether or not to startup AURP.

wfAppleAurpBaseState.name: wfAppleAurpBaseState
wfAppleAurpBaseState.description: This parameter relfects the current state of AURP.

wfAppleAurpBaseDomain.name: wfAppleAurpBaseDomain
wfAppleAurpBaseDomain.description: The domain identfier for the domain that this router resides in.

wfAppleAurpBaseIpAddress.name: wfAppleAurpBaseIpAddress
wfAppleAurpBaseIpAddress.description: The IP address configured on this router that AURP should use for all of its connections

wfAppleAurpBaseInAcceptedOpenReqs.name: wfAppleAurpBaseInAcceptedOpenReqs
wfAppleAurpBaseInAcceptedOpenReqs.description: The number of Open Requests that were accepted.

wfAppleAurpBaseInRejectedOpenReqs.name: wfAppleAurpBaseInRejectedOpenReqs
wfAppleAurpBaseInRejectedOpenReqs.description: The number of Open Requests that were rejected.

wfAppleAurpBaseInRouterDowns.name: wfAppleAurpBaseInRouterDowns
wfAppleAurpBaseInRouterDowns.description: The number of Router Down packets that were received.

wfAppleAurpBaseInPktsNoPeers.name: wfAppleAurpBaseInPktsNoPeers
wfAppleAurpBaseInPktsNoPeers.description: The number of packets received from UDP for which there is no valid connection.

wfAppleAurpBaseInInvalidVerions.name: wfAppleAurpBaseInInvalidVerions
wfAppleAurpBaseInInvalidVerions.description: The number of invalid version error received on this tunnel.

wfAppleAurpTable.name: wfAppleAurpTable
wfAppleAurpTable.description: Each AURP connection has an entry in this table

wfAppleAurpEntry.name: wfAppleAurpEntry
wfAppleAurpEntry.description: An entry in the AURP connection table.

wfAppleAurpEntryDelete.name: wfAppleAurpEntryDelete
wfAppleAurpEntryDelete.description: Create/Delete para1meter. Users perform an SNMP SET operation on this object to create/delete an AppleTalk AURP interface. The default is create.

wfAppleAurpEntryDisable.name: wfAppleAurpEntryDisable
wfAppleAurpEntryDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter. Users perforn an SNMP SET operation on this object to enable/disable an AppleTalk AURP interface. Default is enabled.

wfAppleAurpEntryState.name: wfAppleAurpEntryState
wfAppleAurpEntryState.description: The current state of the Aurp Entry.

wfAppleAurpEntryIpAddress.name: wfAppleAurpEntryIpAddress

wfAppleAurpEntryZoneFilterType.description: controls zone filtering on this interface. An allow indicates that any wfAppleZoneFilterEntry is a zone that is allowed on the interface. A deny indicates that any ZoneFilterEntry is a zone that should not be advertised out this interface. No ZoneFilterEntrys indicates that all nets and zones are being advertised.

wfAppleAurpEntrySuiFlags.name: wfAppleAurpEntrySuiFlags
wfAppleAurpEntrySuiFlags.description: The Send Update Information flags. This value matches the 16 bit field sent in OReq and RI-Req packets. The bits are broken down as follows: 0x4000 = Net Add 0x2000 = Net Delete/Net Route Change 0x1000 = Net Distance Change 0x0800 = Zone Change These should be 'OR'ed together for desired updates. e.g. for all updates 0x4000 | 0x2000 | 0x1000 | 0x8000 = 0x7800 = 30720
